    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Spiritist's Spell Ring</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Spiritist's Spell Ring">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white><br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classes:</b></font> Any<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Recommended Level</b>:</font> 60<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Quest Rating:</b></font> 

Good


<br>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Starting NPC:</b></font> <a style="color:#ffffff" href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqbestiaryfull&eqbestiary.mob_name=%22Spiritist%20Kama%20Resan%22">Spiritist Kama Resan</a><br>

<b><font color=#d2d200>Starting Zone:</font></b> Acrylia Caverns<br>








<br><b>Related NPCs:</b><br><a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqbestiaryfull&eqbestiary.mob_name=%22A%20Reanimated%20Prisoner%22">A Reanimated Prisoner</a><br>


<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqbestiaryfull&eqbestiary.mob_name=%22A%20Warder%20of%20Life%22">A Warder of Life</a><br>


<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqbestiaryfull&eqbestiary.mob_name=%22Khati%20Sha%20the%20Twisted%22">Khati Sha the Twisted</a><br>


<br><b>Reward(s)</b>:<br>
<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Bone Ring of the Life Ward%22">Bone Ring of the Life Ward</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Trinket of Life%22">Trinket of Life</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Longbow of the Grimlings%22">Longbow of the Grimlings</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Lifebane Wristguards%22">Lifebane Wristguards</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Deathguard's Pauldrons%22">Deathguard's Pauldrons</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Orb of Death%22">Orb of Death</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Silken Cords of Life%22">Silken Cords of Life</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Twisted Chain Boots%22">Twisted Chain Boots</A><br>


<br>
<font color=#d2d200><b>Description:</b></font><br>
This is a ring/trial type of event that is perhaps the most challenging event on Luclin. There is a thread on this event at <a href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=6504.topic">The Safehouse</a>.<BR><BR>It is initiated in the jail cells in Acrylia Caverns. This is the room where the Arch Sage spawns. You will need to split your raid in to two groups. One will be down in this area, and the other will be up top in the room with the Sacrificial Cauldron.<BR><BR>You must first clear both jail cells down below and the pot room up top before you begin this event. Then tell Spiritst Kama Resan that you are "ready to begin our spell" to initiate the event.<BR><BR>At that point 3 spell jammers will spawn in each jail cell down below. These mobs will prevent the Spiritist from casting their spells, so must be taken out immediately. Skeletons will also be summoned at this point but ignore them(mesmerize) until the jammers are all down. After they are down finish off the skeletons.<BR><BR>There are three waves, with six jammers in each wave. After completing these three waves A Warder of Life will become targetable in the center of the two jail cells. He will immediately attempt to kill the Spiritists, you can not allow this to happen or you will fail the event(and the room will respawn completely, likely killing everybody). He is level 65. You will probably want to keep a tank in the middle of the cells to gain aggro on him as soon as he becomes targetable. If you do not do it immediately he will kill the Spiritists and you will fail. Kill him and he will drop some items and the Life Ward will be complete.<BR><BR>While this is happening the Death Ward will also begin upstairs in the Sacrificial Cauldron room. A Warder of Death will spawn. He is slowable and has an area effect DoT which will cause spells to cast slower as well as doing some damage over time. This is the boss of this the Death Ward. If he reaches the cauldron then you have failed.<BR><BR>There are also several sacrifices who will spawn right at the cauldron. You must aggro these immediately to avoid them reaching the cauldron. If they get to the cauldron the Warder of Death will be complletey healed. AE stun is a good idea here and tanks to off-tank them. These are not messable. While they are being off-tanked have the rest of this portion of the raid kill the Warder. After he is dead you can finish these off.<BR><BR>The death ward should be complete before the life ward is. You can then head downstairs and help those at the Life Ward.<BR><BR>After completing both the Life and the Death ward the floor in the Warlord's room will unlock. You can head to that room and click on the floor to open it. This is the Spirit Ward.<BR><BR>We don't have complete details on the spirit ward at this time, but here is what we do know. If you want to submit further information you may do so by <a href="mailto:erasmushurt@earthlink.net">clicking here</a>.<BR><BR>You will need to choose which of the two Vah Shir to save. If you choose the one on the right he will kill the other and an Elite Grimling Guard will spawn and open the next door. You then will need to make your way across a large lava pool. After this a good number of Grimling Elites will spawn and attack you. If you manage to get past this point you will be greeted with Khati Sha the Twisted, the toughest mob on Luclin. He has his own loot table.<br><br>



